content.description:
Sack Lunch climbs a short, vertical face on thin, high quality edges.

Stand start just left of the tree with a pair of incut edges about seven feet off the ground. From there, reach a right hand edge, then move both hands to a pair of incut slopers below the lip, reach the subsequent lip, and top it out.
content.protection: A pad will work, the landing is good, but there is a small tree off to the side.
content.location: It climbs the northeast face of Chunnel.

content.description: Stand start with a horizontal, left hand edge and a high, right hand toothy-sidepull. From there, reach the crimp rail, match on it, then negotiate the lip, and top it out.
content.protection: A pad will do, the landing is very good.
content.location: It climbs the northeast face of Chunnel.

content.description: Stand start with hands matched on a edge about seven feet off the ground. From there, climb straight on good edges.
content.protection: A pad or two will do, the immediate fall zone is great, there is a rock behind the problem though.
content.location: It climbs the northeast face of Chunnel.

content.description: Stand start with a left hand edge and a right hand gaston about seven feet off the deck. From there, climb straight up the vertical face on good edges to reach the topout.
content.protection: A pad will do, the landing is very good.
content.location: It climbs the northeast face of Chunnel.
